<Author>themilkybarkid
<Content>Perfect location Stayed here for 5 nights to attend a conference - I was in room 527 at the front of the hotel.The room was a little small but had the benefit of a good sized balcony with table and chair great for chilling out, sunbathing enjoying a drink.No tea or coffee making facilities so if you fancy a drink take your own bottle opener and snacks! You could use the mini-bar in your room but I guess it's probably pretty expensive. The room has a decent bathroom with all you'd want. The room was serviced every day and left immaculate.What makes this hotel recommended is:1. The Location - it's just off the Cataluyna Plaza which is the heart of all the transport links. The metro line is superb - buy a ticket with 20 journey's it's much cheaper. You can also get the airport bus direct from the Plaza. Just off the plaza is the famous La Ramblas. The Plaza and La Ramblas are very busy popular areas but this hotel is just off in what is surprisingly a quiet street.2. The Breakfast (food and the service) - buffet eat as much as you like with a very wide range always kept in good supply, always tidied and kept neat. In fact the staff are just so attentive, warm and provide an excellent service. Topping up your coffee is no hassle someone is floating around all the time looking after you. The food is good quality. The freshly baked cakes and donuts are highly recommended! 3. The Pool - on the first floor there is an open air (small) swimming pool -surrounded by gardens, trees, shrubs with a good supply of chairs and sun bed. Towels provided too. This is a lovely relaxing haven from busy city life.4. The Architecture - the hotel was designed by Gaudi's teacher - the doorwar and staircase has all the hallmarks.5. The staff - all pleasant and helpful - especially breakfast staff.The only downside was that the aircon didn't seem to be working - so a huge vertical fan was installed in my room which was fine - left on too long air con leaves me with a dry throat.The room was a little small -but they are all different.But I'd recommend this hotel! 
