<Author>david-the-banker
<Content>Don't understand the poor ratings - good stay Now I can't comment on value for money because I was staying as a guest of the Barcelona Ocean Racing Foundation. And maybe being hooked into a major Barcelona sporting event got me privileged treatment BUTI was originally in a room overlooking the admittedly quiet street but asked for and got a room change to overlook the central courtyard - which was blissfully peaceful. The room was big enough, clean, comfortable and well equipped - although I didn't get the bathrobe and slippers that I had at the sister hotel (Catalonia Ramblas) previously. The breakfast was excellent. We drank in the bar - which was very quiet and where service had to be summoned by a bell. But the bartender was competent enough. My colleague reported that the dinner he had in the hotel restaurant was good. The reception staff were slightly defensive about the hotel - which is old and which was renovated some time ago unlike the Catalonia Ramblas. But all the fixtures and fitings were modern, the TV had all the cable channels etc. The staff were proud of the historical connections with the architect who actually was Gaudi's teacher. And the hall well up to the bar had all its art deco features retained - very nicely done. I thought that although the rooms were clearly older than at the Catalonia Ramblas they were more practical - there were hooks on the back of doors, plenty of coathangers etc. I got on with the Lithuanian/Slovakian/Ukrainian/Spanish reception staff. So for my weekend stay the hotel gets a clean bill of health. I would go back. 
