<Content>Fantastic Location We stayed at the Catalonia Duques de Bergara for a 3 night break. The hotel is in a great location by Plaza de Catalunya. It's the perfect location for the Ramblas, or to walk to the more upmarket areas of Eixample. The hotel is just off the main square. There are numerous great shops within a stones throw of the hotel. Our room was on the top floor facing the main road and we had virtually no street noise thanks to quality double glazing. The room itself was very small, but that said it was clean, comfortable, and had all the features you'd expect. We were on the 5th floor and had a huge balcony which got the sun for most of the day and gave you great views of the city. The hotel provides breakfast. If you're a big eater go for it. It has the usual cooked breakfast, cheeses, cold meats, fruit and cereal, all of which were excellent. The only down side being the coffee which unusually for Spain was not good! The pool is lovely and a great retreat after a day walking around the city.If you book ask for a room away from the cleaners cupboards. Our's was opposite it and it did get a bit noisy from about 8am.In summary a great location, good food, excellent facilities and a great base for seeing Barcelona. 
