<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Perfect choice for a stay in Barcelona We (family with 15 year old daughter) just returned from a two week stay in this (beautifully styled) hotel. We had one double and one twin room on the top (6th) floor, both with a large balcony on the street side. We enjoyed the spacious, airconditioned rooms and the luxurious, marble bathrooms. Rooms were bright and clean and contained, apart from a minibar and TV, a wall-cupboard with sufficient space for all our clothes. Each room costed us about 鈧?100,- per room per night, incl. taxes, which is certainly not expensive for this (4-star-)standard.Breakfast in this hotel may be a bit expensive (鈧?13 p.p.) , but the buffet offers everything you can imagine (scrambled eggs, saucages, muesli, cheese, hams, marmelades, fruits, fresh fruit juices and, of course, coffee nd tea). Especially for people who like to fill their plates several times, this price cannot be beaten. In case you only breakfast with a croissant and coffee, you'd better take one of the bars or cervecerias at the nearby Rambla Catalunya.The hotel is ideally located in a quiet side street just off Plaza Catalunya and we doubt there is a better priced hotel with the same quality in central Barcelona.The (small) swimming pool is a nice addition, even though the chairs are mostly occupied when you return from the city after 3 pm. The service of the staff is OK. The receptionists are very helpful (e.g. when my wallet with credit cards was stolen downtown). The restaurant offers a good choice of Spanish cuisine, although the atmosphere is a bit too formal, which is about the only (slight) criticism we have on this hotel.In all respects: a perfect choice for a stay in Barcelona. 
